properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued February 7 at 11:03AM CST until February 9 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...SNOW EXPECTED LATE SATURDAY NIGHT INTO SUNDAY ACROSS SOUTHERN
MINNESOTA INTO WISCONSIN...

.A winter storm watch for moderate to heavy snow remains in effect for
southern Minnesota into Wisconsin, along and south of a line from
Redwood Falls to Red Wing Minnesota to Eau Claire Wisconsin from
late Saturday night into Sunday. Most locations will see 3 to 6
inches, but there will be a narrow band of 5 to 8 inches of snow.
The heaviest snow will be Sunday morning.

The winter storm watch means be prepared, hazardous winter
weather is possible. Travel impacts are expected as roads become
snow covered and slippery. Winds will be fairly light, with only
minor blowing or drifting.

* WHAT...Moderate to heavy snow possible. Total snow
accumulations of 5 to 7 inches possible.

* WHERE...Redwood, Brown, Watonwan and Martin Counties.

* WHEN...From late Saturday night through Sunday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and impacts to
travel.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM LATE SATURDAY NIGHT THROUGH SUNDAY AFTERNOON
